    "The similar pattern can be observed for a total training time, which decreased to 56-71% of the FFT training time.",
    "(4) Saving computational costs results in lower performance, some exceptions, however, exist.",
    "Saving the VRAM usage and shortening training time is naturally reflected in the lower performance compared to that of FFT.",
    "Adapters are consistently outperformed by FFT in all three sub-tasks.",
